We recommended that Management ascertain the recorded Local Road Network through the following:
1.1 General Services Officer /Municipal Treasurer (MT) to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;
1.2 Municipal Accountant (MA) to trace the recorded road, highways and bridges which were closed to government equity prior to 2016 and subsequently record in its books of accounts the amount of road works equivalent to the required transition provision, keep and maintain Registry of Public Infrastructures for Road and subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and provide for the depreciation for the local road network;
1.3 Municipal Engineer (ME) to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
1.4 MA to include in the Notes to Financial Statements necessary details of the local roads recorded in the books as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct:
1. The General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;  
2. The Municipal Accountant to trace the recorded road, highways and bridges which were closed to government equity prior to 2016 and subsequently record in its books of accounts the amount of road works equivalent to the required transition provision, keep and maintain Registry of Public Infrastructures for Road and subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and provide for the depreciation for the local road network; 
3. The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
4. The Municipal Accountant to include in the Notes to Financial Statements necessary details of the local roads recorded in the books as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008.
