We have recommended the following:
 That the Municipal Treasurer be instructed to suspend the payment of salaries of the officials and employees concerned for the restitution of unliquidated cash advances;
 That management strengthen the operation of preventive and monitoring controls to ensure timely submission of liquidation reports and supporting documents;
 That the Municipal Accountant send final demand letters to those former employees with outstanding cash advances requesting for the liquidation or refund of cash advances granted to them; and
 That the disbursement vouchers pertaining to the grant of cash advances and copies of demand letters be submitted to the Auditor for proper action. For the cash advances where the person liable is already deceased, management may request for authority to write off the amount in accordance with the provisions of COA Memorandum No. 2002-053 and Rule VI of the 2009 Revised Rules of Procedure of the Commission on Audit.

